findingsText:
 1. developed Electrical Impedance Tomography (EIT) technique for lung imaging in Intensive Care Unit (ICU) for critically-ill patient;

2. Used the information provided by the images to design a decision support system that administers therapy to ICU patients to help them breath on their own. The findings can be exploited in two-fold:

1. Use the electronic system based around Electrical Impedance Tomography (EIT) to develop a portable system that takes images of the patient lungs in a flexible and economic way;

2. Embed this EIT-based imaging system within a more integrated architecture that advises on 'optimal' therapy for ICU patients. Education,Electronics,Healthcare
